  "prompt": "I scored 570 in neet 2 . What would be my expected rank, in total from neet 1 & 2?",
  "response": "To provide a more accurate estimate of your expected rank, I would need some additional context. The NEET (National Eligibility cum Entrance Test) exam in India typically doesn't have \"NEET 1\" and \"NEET 2.\" Instead, it is a single national-level entrance examination conducted once a year. \n\nAssuming by \"NEET 2,\" you are referring to a hypothetical second NEET exam or an attempt, typically only the score from the latest or best attempt is considered for the final merit list, not an average of multiple exams. If you have taken multiple attempts, they usually consider the best score.\n\nFor a more precise answer, please clarify what you mean by \"NEET 1\" and \"NEET 2.\" Also, NEET ranks can greatly fluctuate each year based on the difficulty level of the exam, overall performance of candidates, and the number of candidates appearing for the exam. It is advisable to compare your score against the official rank lists from previous years to get an approximate idea. Generally, a score of 570 might rank within the range of approximately 15,000 to 25,000, but this is speculative and can vary each year.",
